						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1304</hi> (mistake for 1330), <hi rend="bold">Sarvadhāri, Mārgaśira, śu. 7, Budhavāra.</hi> The date is not regular; Sarvadhāri corresponded to A.D. 1408-09. The inscription refers itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Hiryia-Dēvarāya (I)</hi> and records the grant of a village (name lost) with its toll-revenue for the service of god <hi rend="bold">Hanumantadēva.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
